Section 1 Mission
Purpose

The USOP Commercial Licensing Architecture establishes a trustworthy commercial relationship between the Open Secure Operations Platform (USOP) and its customers while preserving complete customer ownership of identities, infrastructure, governance, operational security data, secrets, audit history, and institutional knowledge.

Commercial licensing validates software entitlement.

Commercial licensing does not establish operational trust.

Commercial licensing does not authenticate users.

Commercial licensing does not authorize actions.

Commercial licensing does not replace enterprise identity providers.

Commercial licensing does not define governance policy.

Commercial licensing does not require privileged vendor access.

Instead, commercial licensing provides a cryptographically verifiable statement describing the commercial capabilities a customer is entitled to operate while remaining entirely independent of operational security.

USOP customers own their security environment.

USOP provides software, commercial entitlement, documentation, updates, and support.

The Commercial Licensing Architecture exists to preserve that separation for the lifetime of the platform.

Section 2 Product Vision

USOP is an Enterprise Security Decision Platform.

Its purpose is not to replace existing security technologies.

Its purpose is to transform evidence produced by those technologies into organizational knowledge that enables faster, more consistent, and better-informed security decisions.

Commercial licensing exists solely to establish commercial entitlement for that platform.

Operational security remains entirely under customer control.

Customers should never be required to surrender ownership of identities, infrastructure, governance, secrets, or operational data in order to validate commercial licensing.

